costume: As a recent graduate in the arts of Geomancy, Hikaru travels the world in search of adventure while developing his own unique style of martial arts.
A Elvan prince skilled in the arts of planar magic. Khadath seeks a new world for his cursed people, some place beyond the reach of an angry god.
Wielding the legendary Sword of Saint Kelbran, Eligor serves as a Templar--Judge, Jury, and Executioner under the holy laws of Ka-Shin.
Once, she was a simple thief, stealing treasures for the highest bidder. When she stole the cursed Claw of Malephaise, everything changed.
After defeating the overlord Rexan three centuries ago, Luc Von Gott headed to the future to thwart an even more dire calamity.
Before he was a professor of alchemy, Riflam traveled the world in search of hidden wisdom. Now, he wields his fighting skills in defense of that ancient lore.

Doppelgangers were not the only strange creatures to emerge from the twisted realms of the Minus World. Despite that it's not yet clear what Seven is, the magisters of Willat saw in her the potential for a weapon.
The thirty-seventh king of Jeffreys, Alexian is said to be descended from the ancient giants. Though a king in peacetime, he foresees a shadow of war growing in the nations around him.

The feral are blessed by the gods of the wild with the power to transform into beasts. For Karin and her twin brother Jager, this blessing is also a curse, for they may never take the same form at once.

Elemental-touched humans are not rare in Indines, but few have mastered the power in their heritage like Kallistar. A master of Sorcery, Kallistar studies the ancient art of War Magic under Dean Larimore Burman.
Clockwork soldiers like this one form the core of the Willati armed forces. This prototype model is directly controlled by Magister Bors Vilnar, inventor of the line.
An outcast in his homeland, due to his inability to use magic, Rukyuk carved a niche for himself as an ace bounty hunter. Now he tracks down men and monsters that pose a threat to his homeland.
Knights of Lesion wear cursed armor and wield blades filled with dread magic. Immune to magic themselves, they reap only the benefits of these cursed treasures.
An agent of the Reliquary, César is tasked with recovering dangerous artifacts. His golem heart makes him a tireless servant of his masters, much to his chagrin.

Archmage Kimbhe of Relecour has heard tales of ancient power sleeping beneath the surface of the world. To prevent it from falling into the wrong hands, she has taken up her staff and joined the fight.

Not content to lead from the rear, Sarafina takes her technology and fighting skills to the front lines to do battle against villains who threaten her country - whether they be outsiders or her fellow rulers.
Hoping to prevent the return of ancient tragedies, Marmelee seeks to stop those who would free her imprisoned father: the tyrant dragon Greyheart.
Channeling the spirit of the legendary hero Avenlia, the priestess Magdelina departs on a crusade to stop the prophecied return of a dark overlord.
With his mastery of the martial arts complete, Hikaru set about creating his own style–the way of the four fists.
The planestalkers had taught Khadath much about travel between the worlds. Now, his adventures would take him even further, and he needed to be prepared.
With his commission from King Alexian as Lord Templar, Eligor now served as both a guardian and spiritual advisor to the crown princess, Merjoram.
Even though the Daemons had been defeated, Shekhtur knew her adventures weren't over yet. She smiled down at the claw on her left hand, knowing that she was master of her own fate.
The original temporal battery designs were effective, but crude. Luc was confident this new model would be an unparalleled success.
As chancellor of Argent University, Riflam found that his duties included not just education, but also the defense of ancient mystical secrets.
Magister Looma continued to delve deeper into the mysteries of the void, but what she found there she could not dare to write.
At last, with the overlord Rexan vanquished, Alexian's quest was complete. Now, to bring civilization to the savage lands of the south.
With the blessing of the Wolf-King, Karin was at least free of her human form. Now, the moon calls, and the hunt begins...
"You've learned well." Dean Burman handed Kallistar a war mage's mantle, fashioned in the same style as his own. "I hope you understand the consequences of such knowledge."
The finishing touches were complete on the Mark VI. The only thing left for Vilnar to do was to find a worthy mission for a field test...
Mercenary work paid the bills, but Rukyuk was tired of fighting for the rich. By founding his own free company, the Champions of Indines, he hoped to fight for all the people of Indines.
Centuries had passed, but César's resolve never faltered. The promise he made to Arlant would never be forgotten, even though the world had forgotten her long ago.
When you're the archmage, you can wear pretty much whatever you want and there's nobody that can stop you.
With Vilnar's plots thwarted, there was nothing left to stand between Sarafina and her plan to become arch-magister, the one and only supreme ruler of Willat.
As the new dragon queen, Marmelee now had the means and the power to enforce her vision of peace and tolerance throughout the land of Indines.

At last, the conduit was complete, the girl was just a blank slate, and Avenlia had taken full control. Her eyes glistened with power and secrets brought from the afterworld. "Now… let the new crusade begin."
What he had seen across the sea, on the unknown continent, had changed him. Hikaru knew that he had little time to prepare for the task at hand.

After countless worlds and what seemed like an eternity of searching, the Ahemusei tribe finally found a plane to call their own. The journey there had changed Khadath, making him more than a mere mortal...
For his service to the realm, Eligor was awarded a knighthood and a suit of golden armor. As a protector and advisor to Crown Princess Merjoram, he continues to serve his kingdom.
"Give in, and fight me with your real power!" Ariel crowed, standing over the wounded Shekhtur. Could she really win against such a monstrous foe? And at what cost...?

Before he was the legendary hero who defeated the overlord Rexan, he was a genius inventor who sought to unravel the strings of time. With his prototype Temporal Battery, Luc Von Gott made many important discoveries about time travel which are still used by chronomancers today.
With the last of the Infinity Formulae unraveled, all of Indines would soon belong to Riflam... that is, as long as that blasted Captain Hikaru didn't interfere...
Deep within her core, Seven could feel all the missing pieces of the world fighting to be reborn. She couldn't hold back the tide any longer...
Alexian the First's brother, Camber, fell in love with the Daemon Sera Malephaise and abdicated the throne to join her in the Afterworld. Then they lived happily ever after.

"I want you to stay with me. To be my voice to the human world, to be my defender... and also, my friend." Marmelee confessed. Karin didn't need to think about her answer, and merely embraced her best friend.
Argent's dueling club is a popular extracurricular activity. Only three casualties last year!
"Flesh and bone are weak materials to build on. Now this... this is a canvas I can use to create a soldier!" Hepzibah crowed as she began her newest experiment.
Magister Vanedran's cybernetic improvements heightened his senses, and the new weapons were unlike anything he had seen. He only hoped that it would be enough to stop August before it was too late.
When Uleyle hits the dance floor, nobody stands a chance against her. Try to steal her groove, and you'll be hit by the electric slide!
Kerigan Corporation controls all aspects of life in the future city of Neo-Willat, but they can't stop the mysterious anarchist Vanedran from keeping the music alive!
The megacorps of Neo-Willat have been thrown into chaos more than once by the hacker known only as MARMS. Her one and only weakness is being easily distracted by internet memes.
Using the power of the elements, Captain Hikaru defends Indines from those who would exploit its natural resources for their selfish gain. Remember: "The Power is yours!"
The students of Argent tell stories of a terrifying specter that haunts Kor Karoli on the nights of the red moon. When you hear the barghest howl, it's already too late...
The interplanar invasion of the Cadenzabots will eventually destroy all of Indines. Only Welsie Acktern and the Masters of Time (TM) stand in the way of their total domination.
Princess Uleyle thought she was the last of the Sorcerans, a mightly race of alien warriors with uncanny powers. But the people of Terra had a big surprise in store for her…
Staring into the void at the end of the universe changed Sarafina. With this power, she would carry out the wishes of her new masters…

Her journeys soon brought Magdelina to Sanghalim, the ancient land of myths and the birthplace of the gods. As a student of the Imperial Monastery, she descended into the sacred crypts to meet her ancestor and spirit guardian.
According to the will of his divine masters, Mikhail defends the world of Indines against the forces of chaos and despair.
"I'll no longer be swayed by powers and prejudices from another age. I'll fight for the world I believe in--a world of balance."
As the celestial commands filled his mind, his mission was now clear. Nothing could be allowed to stand between this world and the destiny his holy masters had set out for it.
After a thousand-year slumber, an ancient force of destruction stirs, and its harbinger awakens. Anath labors to prepare the world for a disaster unrivaled in the history of Indines...
With Havoc arisen and the world thrown into chaos, Anath finally had all the time and power she needed to destroy the outsiders who had despoiled Indines...
Only when the last of the Chaons is in captivity, will the galaxy finally be at peace.
After the fall, the means to survive became scarce. As one of the few who claimed power over the old gods of fire and lightning, Anath quickly amassed a following. Then, the raids began.

product: War stirs between the kingdom of Jeffreys and the empire of Gesselheim. The time has come for King Alexian to take up his blade and fight!
At last, with the overlord Rexan vanquished, Alexian's quest was complete. Now, to bring civilization to the savage lands of the south.
Alexian the First's brother, Camber, fell in love with the Daemon Sera Malephaise and abdicated the throne to join her in the Afterworld. Then they lived happily ever after.
The Cadenza line of clockwork knights were created by Magister Bors Vilnar. This unit, personally controlled by Vilnar, is outfitted with a wide array of special weapons.
The finishing touches were complete on the Mark VI. The only thing left for Vilnar to do was to find a worthy mission for a field test...
"Flesh and bone are weak materials to build on. Now this... this is a canvas I can use to create a soldier!" Hepzibah crowed as she began her newest experiment.
The templars are an ancient order of wandering judges who serve the kingdom of Jeffreys. Though his duty is to the law, Eligor's ambition is fame and fortune.
When he closed his eyes, he could still see the ruins of his home. Kerhault would be avenged, and there would be no rest until every one of those monsters was dead.
The fame and glory had not diminished his spirit of adventure. Donning his sacred armor, Eligor once again set out on a new quest...
Adventurers roam the continent of Indines, seeking thrills, fortune, and glory. What trials and triumphs await on the journey of such an explorer?
After wandering the continent from east to west, Hikaru set his sights on a new challenge–the unexplored lands beyond the horizon.
What he had seen across the sea, on the unknown continent, had changed him. Hikaru knew that he had little time to prepare for the task at hand.
Half-Elementals are closely bonded with the essence of magic. In Kallistar's case, her firey heritage lends itself to the destructive side of spellcasting.
"You've learned well." Dean Burman handed Kallistar a war mage's mantle, fashioned in the same style as his own. "I hope you understand the consequences of such knowledge."
Argent's dueling club is a popular extracurricular activity. Only three casualties last year!
Hepzibah's spell had saved Kallistar's life, but it had changed her. For the first time, she felt a chill creep down through her fingertips...
Bonded at birth to her werewolf brother Jager, the two share only one human soul and one wolf soul between them. Together, they hope to find a way to break their curse.
With the blessing of the Wolf-King, Karin was at least free of her human form. Now, the moon calls, and the hunt begins...

"I want you to stay with me. To be my voice to the human world, to be my defender... and also, my friend." Marmelee confessed. Karin didn't need to think about her answer, and merely embraced her best friend.

On the night of the red moon, a terrible phantom stalks the streets of Kor Karoli with a bloody cleaver in hand and the hounds of hell at her beck and call. At least, that's the legend the seniors tell new freshmen at Argent University.
The Ahemusei tribe was dying. To escape their fate, one young man set out on a journey to find a new land, beyond the reach of the gods and their curse...
The planestalkers had taught Khadath much about travel between the worlds. Now, his adventures would take him even further, and he needed to be prepared.
As the third sun rose over the great crystal mountains, the Ahemusei chieftan rose from his meditation. He had found this land of promise, and he would not let it be taken from his people.
After saving the world from the clutches of the villainous overlord Rexan, Luc traveled through time to a future age where he could once more play the role of a hero.
The original temporal battery designs were effective, but crude. Luc was confident this new model would be an unparalleled success.
He was only a young scientist living in Jeffreys when the war began, but Luc knew that he had to do his part to fight against the overlord's tyranny.
Every alchemist embarks on a journey of discovery, to learn about and comprehend the world around him. Through Riflam's adventures have ended, he still works to teach and guide others.
As chancellor of Argent University, Riflam found that his duties included not just education, but also the defense of ancient mystical secrets.
As the last of the celesial sprockets slotted into place, Riflam could feel the gauntlet surge with infinite power. Indines was his, and no one could stand in his way...
Mercenaries like Rukyuk make their living fighting for the rich and hunting bounties across Indines. This sharpshooter has yet to meet a target his trusty custom ammunition couldn't take down.
Mercenary work paid the bills, but Rukyuk was tired to fighting for the rich. By founding his own free company, the Champions of Indines, he hoped to fight for all the people of Indines.
Magister Vanedran's cybernetic improvements heightened his senses, and the new weapons were unlike anything he had seen. He only hoped that it would be enough to stop August before it was too late.

Mysterious things often emerge from the planes, and Seven is among the strangest. Able to absorb emotional energy and alter her abilities accordingly, this empath proves as formidible as she is enigmatic.
Magister Looma continued to delve deeper into the mysteries of the void, but what she found there she could not dare to write.
Deep within her core, Seven could feel all the missing pieces of the world fighting to be reborn. She couldn't hold back the tide any longer...

The relics of Malephaise bind themselves to mortals, slowly corrupting their souls and producing Daemons. Though she has been bound to the Claw of Malephaise, Shekhtur has resolved to use this power for good, rather than evil.
Even though the Daemons had been defeated, Shekhtur knew her adventures weren't over yet. She smiled down at the claw on her left hand, knowing that she was master of her own fate.
"Don't fight it any longer, give in to your true nature!" Ariel roared. As the two clashed in battle, Shekhtur knew that the only way to win was to let the left claw's full power consume her...

Welcome to BATTLECON ONLINE ALPHA version 0.12.0 ! Released on February 27th, 2018 Welcome back to another round of patching! This week we introduce quests and updated rewards, as well as Marmelee! Our next patch is scheduled for March 20th!

New Fighter

Marmelee Greyheart Marmelee is a control mage who specializes in shutting down enemy attacks, minimizing damage or sneaking in precise stuns. Like Luc, she gains her Concentration Counters at the end of every turn and can spend them on optional effects. These effects let her ruin the enemy's attacks - either by stunning, dodging, negating, or forcing them out of range. - Marmelee's Bonus Costume, is pending and should be available next patch. - Marmelee's Voiceovers are still being produced. So until our next update, she'll be speaking telepathically. We apologize for the delays, and hope to catch up on all the missing VOs in the next patch or two.

Balance Changes

With each update, we assess balance and make slight updates in order to improve the balance and playability of the game. We appreciate your feedback, as it helps us to make the best BattleCON Online possible!

Cadenza

- Battery: +3 Priority next beat, from +4 Developer's Notes: We've been monitoring Cadenza for a long time, because his pile of stats and ease of use have made him consistently and generally strong. Rather than hit him too hard, we're starting by making it a bit harder for him to contest fast characters after Battery Dodge or Battery Press, which also slightly nerfs his ability to close games. While this probably won't be a significant hit to power level, we expect it to feel a bit fairer to play against him.

Cesar

- Unstoppable: -1 Priority, from -2. Now has Soak 1, Stun Guard 1. - Suppression: 1 Range, from 1~2 Developer's Notes: Cesar's Suppression at 1~2 Range was a buff from printed that we were testing, but it made certain pairs (Phalanx Suppression) impossible to play against for characters that needed time to ramp. We're bringing Suppression back to its original 1 Range, but giving him a major buff to Priority variance - improved defenses and trading on Unstoppable, especially with its improved Priority, means that opponents need to take more risk when trying to clash him out.

Magdelina

- Excelsius: Move up to 1, from move 1. Developer's Notes: The changes to Excelsius last patch made it feel a lot worse in situations where you would be forced to move and either ruin your push or miss your attack due to the corner. We're still monitoring her overall power level, but this should make Excelsius feel less clunky.

Riflam

- Alchemic: Regain 2 life when spending Reagent, from 1 Developer's Notes: Alchemic has always been Riflam's best defensive Style against heavyweights, and this change will hopefully make him a bit better at contesting them. Riflam struggles in matchups where opponents don't give him time to breathe and buff his Bases effectively, so this will let him burn a bit of ideal lategame in exchange for more survivability.

Other Notes & Bug Fixes

- Fixed a bug which prevented Regal from blocking retreats.

Client Upgrades

- Daily Quests Players will now get daily quests that provide gold! As a side effect of this and in order to improve the play experience for newer players, rewards have been adjusted as follows: - Win: 40 Coins - Loss: 20 Coins - Quests: 50 or 100 Coins - Avatars Avatars can now be changed! The full functionality isn't in yet, but ask a dev if there's anything specific you want and we can make something happen. - Options Menu Redesigned the options menu to have better sound controls and reduce the risk of people accidentally closing their client when trying to concede. - Dev Server Changed the behavior of our development realm to be more user-friendly. Notably, players can't accidentally get stuck forever trying to log in after checking the Dev box. If you want to beta test characters or features, let us know! - Launch Updates Windows players should see significantly reduced launch times. Similar Mac improvements still under investigation.

Minor Improvements

- Finishers now zoom properly on click. - Marmelee art and animations added. - Status Effects are no longer shown in the initial Cards wheel, which cuts down on extraneous cards for characters like Magdelina or Riflam. - Fixed some crashes. - Added improved animation for Move Directly.

Welcome to BATTLECON ONLINE ALPHA version 0.11.0! Released on February 6th, 2018 Welcome back to another round of patching! This week we introduce the in-client store, plus Cesar is here! Our next patch is scheduled for February 27th!

New Fighter

Cesar Grist, the Reliquary Hunter Cesar's a cyclical fighter who gains extreme power, then shuts down and gives up the next beat. As he continues to cycle through the game, watch out for his extremely dangerous corner traps and his ability to utterly ruin opponents who predict wrong on his power beats. - Cesar's Bonus Costume, is pending and should be available next patch. - Cesar's Voiceovers are still being produced. So until our next update, he'll be speaking telepathically.

Balance Changes

With each update, we assess balance and make slight updates in order to improve the balance and playability of the game. We appreciate your feedback, as it helps us to make the best BattleCON Online possible!

Magdelina

- Excelsius: Range to +0, from +0~1 - Sanctimonious: Range to +0~1, from +0. Range down to +0~1 per 2 Concentration, round down. - Priestess: Life is gained On Hit rather than After Activating. Developer's Notes: Magdelina's been running the top tables since her release, due to her safe midgame covering her mediocre earlygame very well. These changes should emphasize that her ranges are definitely her weakness, and limit her opportunities to immediately win free beats at Level 2 using Excelsius. Priestess change also refocuses that as an anti-Heavyweight tool rather than "the Style you pair with Dodge for free life".

Shekhtur

- Jugular: Now only gains 1 Malice for free. - Reaver: Push limited to 3 spaces. Developer's Notes: Shekhtur's been particularly strong for a while, and this is aimed at cutting some extraneous power. Jugular is amazing, but it's such a strong safety net that Shekhtur's opponents often feel like there is no window to punish her if she runs low on Malice. This should still feel good to play, but the worst-case is now much more concerning for Shekhtur. Reaver push change reduces the odds of some low-counterplay situations where she could set up guaranteed beats with Jugular Shot afterwards and the opponent would whiff this beat due to a huge (4 space) push.

Seven

- Sympathetic: Now has +0~1 Range, from +0 - Detached: Now has +0~1 Range, from +0; now has After: Move up to 1. - Absorption: Now has "Seven cannot take more than 4 damage." Developer's Notes: Seven's early game against high Power characters was particularly rough, and this is aimed at smoothing that out. The buff to Sympathetic should help her a bit when closing out games.

Other Notes & Bug Fixes

- Fixed a bug which prevented Seven's opponents from properly retreating. - Fixed a bug which prevented first ante from updating properly. - Fixed a bug with Eligor's Stun Immunity ante.

Client Upgrades

- Disconnect Concession. A player who is disconnected from the game for too long will automatically concede, fixing a number of "hung game" issues we were experiencing. - Shop. Purchases are now far better organized! You can also buy groups of characters as a discounted bundle. - Prep work for Quests. Quests will be released next patch! As both a guide for what people might want to play and an extra source of income, we've started laying the groundwork for these. Look out for more information later this month!

Minor Improvements

- Attack animations for Cesar. - Details for "owned" and shop filters. - Hand viewer added during game setup. - Nullification event improved to handle more circumstances - helps with cards like Fueled.

New Fighter

Magdelina Larington, Battle Channeler of Jeffreys! Magdelina gains Trance Counters each turn. Balance Changes

With each update, we assess balance and make slight updates in order to improve the balance and playability of the game. We appreciate your feedback, as it helps us to make the best BattleCON Online possible!

Eligor

- Sheet Lightning Finisher: Now has 5 Power, from 4. Developer's Notes: Sweet Revenge is an extremely strong finisher, and was outshining Sheet Lightning in most circumstances. This should even things out a little.

Khadath

- Snare: Now Ignores Soak if the opponent is standing on the Gate Trap. Developer's Notes: Khadath has typically suffered heavily against tanky characters that can ignore the Priority penalty due to strong defenses. While he can threaten auto-dodge effects, this gives him another angle to play against Eligor and Cadenza, and should make it feel more important that they avoid the Gate Trap.

Luc

- Temporal Recursion Finisher: Advance effect is now Start of Beat, from Before Activating. Now gets +2 Power per Time, instead of +3 Power. Developer's Notes: Temporal Recursion's power level has been skewing Luc balance for a bit, as it is an extremely safe Finisher that can easily pump out 9-12 damage at high Priority and still beat Burst. These changes should make it both easier to play around and less game-ending, while still being a strong game-ender at high Time counts.

Riflam

- Alchemic Style: Now has +0~1 range from +0, now has Hit: May spend reagent to gain 1 life. - Experimental: Now has +1 Power from +0, now has End: If you were hit, apply a reagent without spending it. Before: advance is now optional. - Transformative: Now has Hit: May transform a reagent into another reagent. - Substantial: Now has Hit: Regain a spent reagent. - Grand Arcanum Finisher: Now has 2 Power, from 1. - Arcane Inspiration Finisher: Stats reworked, now 2~3/5/5 Developer's Notes: Riflam's UA never felt particularly integrated with his kit, given the value of his reagent bonuses and how hard it was to get them back. This should allow Riflam to play a much more flexible game, as well as shoring up his power level a bit.

Rukyuk

- Crossfire Style: Now has +1 power from +0, now has Stun Guard 1 in addition to Soak 2. - Force Grenade Finisher: Now has Stun Guard 3. Developer's Notes: Crossfire has always been an awkward style - it does good damage if Rukyuk is willing to spend the ammo, but its minimum range makes it very awkward and its low Priority means that unlike Sniper, it's often possible for the opponent to move out of range before Rukyuk activates. Increasing the Power brings the reward for landing it more in line with its risk, and increasing the Stun Guard means that Rukyuk shouldn't need to ante Force Stun Guard as often. Force Grenade was being outshined by Fully Automatic against a lot of the cast, giving it Stun Guard should make it a much more consistent defensive option against people who have the mobility or priority to play around Fully Automatic.

- Jugular: Now allows Shekhtur to purchase up to 2 Malice for 1 life each instead of resetting to 3 Malice. - Combination: Now has -1 priority from +0. - Brand: Now ignores Stun Guard at 7 Priority rather than 6. Developer's Notes: Shekhtur has been at the top of the metagame for a bit, and these changes are intended to increase her risk if she misses an attack. Jugular is likely still one of the best Styles in the game, and with these changes it should be less attached to Brand. Combination with decreased priority will put a bit more risk into a Style that is currently extremely powerful, meaning that Shekthur needs to ante more and opponents are more rewarded for dodging her big hits.

Just mouse-over the cards in-game to see their tooltips.

Balance Changes:

Burman:

- Blistering: Now has 1 Power, from 2 - Dragonbreath: Now has 1 Power, from 0. Now has "Start: You may spend 2 Firepower to deal 2 life loss the first time opponent Advances this beat." instead of its previous On Hit. - Dragon's Descent: Now has 7 Power, from 8. Now has 1 Priority, from 2. Developer's Notes: This should flatten Burman's power curve somewhat rather than just making him constantly rely on Blistering as the key trading/beat-winning tool. In return, Dragonbreath becomes a lot more favorable at midrange while also giving him a powerful tool to punish predictable advances. Dragon's Descent change opens up more options for Burst to counter it, while slightly reducing its effectiveness. More fine-tuned changes may come later, but we want to see how this plays out.

Magdelina:

- UA: Now loses Trance equal to Level when leveling up (or hitting Level Cap), instead of all Trance. Developer's Notes: One really awkward thing about Magdelina was that Blessing was often useless for gaining Trance, because she would lose the bonus counter if it was used too close to her leveling up. This should open up a lot more opportunities for her to play Blessing during the game. Her actual level up rate is unchanged, outside of Blessing situations.

Kimbhe:

- Expulsion: Now specifies Staff -may- be moved to -unoccupied- space. -Quake: Stun guard to 3 from 4 Developer's Notes: Right now, Expulsion Caster and Expulsion Dodge make it too easy for Kimbhe to regain her Staff, essentially wiping out a lot of potential staff control the opponent could play. This should make her work a bit harder to get that constant +2 Power, and limit her ability to easily close games with Quickening's +4 Priority.

Sarafina:

- Tactical: Now has Hit: You may spend 2 Force for +1 Power. - Locus: Now has Start: If the opponent is on your Projection, Gain 2 Force and Pull 1. - Field: Now has Hit: Gain 2 Force in addition to immobilizing opponent. - Hollow: Now has Damage: Gain 1 Force. - Silver: Now has -1 Power, +1 Priority. - Fulminating Vortex: Now has 7 Power, from 8 - Ritherwhyte Infusion: Now has Hit: Gain 2 Life. Developer's Notes: Tactical, despite having good stats, tended to be underwhelming. Part of this is the amount of power wrapped up in Silver/Implosion at the moment, and part of it is the fact Sarafina never really went in for big damage spikes. These changes give her more resources to play with in terms of cashing out Force for Power as a way to get riskier, more interesting damage as well as generally tapping up her power level.

Seven:

- Cold: Now has +0~1 Range. - Remote: Now has After: Advance up to 1. Developer's Notes: These should make Seven's early-game a little less rough, given how risky her Ranges tend to be at the moment (how easily she can lock herself out of being able to hit). Heated was way better than Cold, so this should help Cold look a bit better in comparison too!
